      <description>&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/68544715478ad.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/685447326416e.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/685447317bf3e.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6854471e8314f.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/68544739b9109.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6854473ad528f.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/68544722171e4.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/68544726b219c.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/685447270b230.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/68544727ac5b6.jpg"/&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Update:&lt;/strong&gt; MAYOR UPDATE - BUG FIX&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;surface map &amp;amp; 15 shrines (pinned on map) were "locked out" due to breaking Robbie's later questline at mid point related to the teleport medallion (tower activation related) and Hero's path (shrine visit and activation related) yet towers, shrines and pins are still visible in the "black screen map" from the get go, underground map kept as previous version, everything warp related works as intended. ( I deeply apologize to users who alread downloaded and got some game progress, to fix this later in the game you need to do some editing in &lt;a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" href="http://macrobledo.com"&gt;macrobledo.com&lt;/a&gt;, check robbie_queslines_fix_guide.rar to see how to fix it)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;em&gt;Bugfix&lt;/em&gt;: broken upgrade quest&lt;br&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;br&gt;Hello again, recently i made a true ng+ savefile for botw, now i present you the ng+ file for TOTK, you still need to complete the tutorial as usual, and get the paraglider from purah, you start in the room of awakening as always with :&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;- autobuild from the start (HOVER BIKE IN FAVORITES, &lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;INFINITE WING AND PORTABLE TOWER IN HISTORY&lt;/span&gt;)&lt;br&gt;- all yiga schematics&lt;br&gt;- all schema stones&lt;br&gt;- all sage's will&lt;br&gt;- some paraglider fabrics&lt;br&gt;- 800 korok seeds (you only need to complete the ones who have the backpack)&lt;br&gt;- boosted mighty zonai sword&lt;br&gt;- true hylian shield 1000 block points&lt;br&gt;- boosted mighty zonai shield &lt;br&gt;- modified zonai shield for shield surf&lt;br&gt;- almost all armours +2 upgrade (exept for one or two, it's a secret)&lt;br&gt;- all zonai devices&lt;br&gt;- all runes except camera &lt;br&gt;- complete hyrule compendium (you still need to get it fixed by Robbie, but after that, all photos are gonna be there)&lt;br&gt;- all locations discovered (fast travel between out in the world shrines enabled, still need to complete the tutorial to unlock the travel as usual, quest hidden shrines are still locked, enabling them breaks their quest) &lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;update : due to Hero's path quest you still need to visit and activate 15 shrines (pinned on map)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;- 4500 zonai charges&lt;br&gt;- some ruppees&lt;br&gt;- some poes&lt;br&gt;- complete depths map unlocked (119/120 lightroots) &lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;update : surface map was removed due to breaking teleport medallion robbie upgrade quest ... the towers are still visble on the "black screen" map&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;- you can buy 10 hearts/ 2 full stamina wheels at the demon statue to unlock the 5th sage or the master sword early without doing any shrine beside the ones at the tutorial or any boss&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;!!!BE WARY, SOME OF THE STRONGEST ENEMY VARIATONS ARE ROAMING THE LAND !!!&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;i do changed a lot of things to make it feel like a proper ng+, while retaining others that could make the whole experience shallow and kinda empty, most ng+ files out there just give you everything and end up breaking stuff later in the game, with this save you can do EVERYTHING you can do in a normal savefile, but now you have some goodies and some extras for your new adventure&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Also if you want a more "classic" zelda experience check out this other mod i made (imo i hate the durability sytem since always) &lt;a href="https://gamebanana.com/mods/601874"&gt;THE SWORD THAT SEALS THE DARKNESS&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;enjoy !&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
