    <item>
      <title>Weapons of Legend Redux</title>
      <author>Real Princess Zelda</author>
      <link>https://gamebanana.com/mods/632271</link>
      <comments>https://gamebanana.com/mods/632271#PostsListModule</comments>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">788c75309f1a597666af42e84c61f6c7973860b8</guid>
      <pubDate>Sat, 15 Nov 2025 01:05:57 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/690ee86355ebb.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/690ee86f07904.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/690ee88146e46.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/690ee8b28fe94.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/690ee897cdd84.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/690ee8c21cdb0.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/690ee8e2f0e81.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/690ee8f8751ef.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/690ee90e07c2c.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/690ee9249b56a.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/690ee931d889d.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/690ee93f682e3.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/690ee976cba6b.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/690ee986f406b.jpg"/&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Update:&lt;/strong&gt; TKCL File&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;I removed the requirement to fight the enemies for Zant's Scimitar and a Mirror Shard due to issues it caused&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;I finally made a TKCL for this mod with the options you can pick from it. If you are using version 2.0.0 rc1 of TKMM, the TKCL file is required due to issues with the latest version.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;em&gt;Overhaul&lt;/em&gt;: The added chests within the Gerudo and Scorched Coliseums no longer require enemies to be defeated&lt;br&gt;&lt;em&gt;Change&lt;/em&gt;: Added a TKCL file with options&lt;br&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;br&gt;Asalazar and Real Princess Zelda have teamed up to create a full remake of the mod &lt;a href="https://gamebanana.com/mods/455944"&gt;Weapons of Legend - Past Zelda Gear&lt;/a&gt;! This mod not only brings back the original 28 weapons, 5 bows, and 21 shields, but also adds an additional 17 weapons, 1 bow, and 2 shields! All now with full fuse compatibility, save flags, proper inventory sorting, and other bug fixes and tweaks!&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;br&gt;IMPORTANT!!!&lt;br&gt;This spreadsheet gives the name, file name, stats, abilities, and general locations of every single weapon, shield, bow, and misc item in this mod! (except the Mirror Essences and Light Arrowhead).&lt;br&gt;This mod has no quests or hints for locations, so this spreadsheet is a useful guide!&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;a href="https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1_lBB4e2ePqkVH0pCVUBMf1hzKJIM7goHi5SzzYBB_Zw/edit?gid=1307063463#gid=1307063463" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;i&gt;Weapons of Legend Redux Spreadsheet&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;&lt;br&gt;What this changes: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;This mod makes many, many changes to the original mod. Not only have I remade all of the weapon icons, but I also edited all weapon models to be fuse compatible, added proper save flags (no more new item pop ups every time you pick up a piece of equipment), fixed a couple broken models, and rebalanced and tweaked certain pieces of equipment, but now every single piece of equipment has a new location/way to collect it to make the process of getting them all more interesting.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Along with this, all pieces of equipment will now appear in 3 different shops in Lookout Landing when collected in the world. One being for weapons, another for shields, and the third for bows. They still need poes, but the Lookout Landing poe statue is no longer touched!&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;More specific changes:&lt;/span&gt; All of the mystical weapons (Master Sword variants) have full glowing blades instead of just the glowing aura. The Zelda II Magical Sword was lengthened to be more in line with the other Master Swords, and the Megaton Hammer was turned into a one handed weapon. All pieces of equipment have also been rebalanced completely, some of which having previous effects removed or effects changed completely along with having different stats. The Razor Sword, for example, has had its durability reduced to 20 and all equipment is breakable by default. Island Lobster Shield (the wooden shield) was made into a metal shield for consistency.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;The music for Hyrule Castle (Ground) and Temple of Time (Sky) were replaced for use in custom locations. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;Changes that were not made: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Many models and icons and text descriptions are left untouched. I redid the icons for all weapons except any shields or bows that return from the previous mod. All weapon models were edited by me except for the shields and all bows (except the Sacred Bow) that return from the previous mod. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;All added equipment:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;This is a list of all of the equipment added to the mod (both returning and new). Keep in mind, any equipment that says it was modified by Real Princess Zelda, that means I did more than just give it fuse compatibility (such as extra significant model edits or texture edits). All 1 handed weapons, 2 handed weapons, and spears were modified by me to give them fuse compatibility. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;&lt;b&gt;The Legend of Zelda: &lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;- White Sword (Hyrule Warriors model)&lt;br&gt;- Magical Sword (Modified Hyrule Warriors model)&lt;br&gt;- Shield of the Hero (Cross Shield) (&lt;a href="https://gamebanana.com/mods/174392"&gt;Pik Model&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;Zelda II: Adventure of Link:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt; - Magical Sword (Issuelink model, modified by Real Princess Zelda)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;A Link to the Past:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;- Fighter's Sword (Asalazar model)&lt;br&gt;- Fighter's Shield (Asalazar model)&lt;br&gt;- Red Shield (Asalazar model)&lt;br&gt;- Master Sword (Issuelink's OoT Master Sword, edited by Tach9)&lt;br&gt;- Mirror Shield (Issuelink model)&lt;br&gt;- Ganon's Trident (Hyrule Warriors model, custom textures by Tach9)&lt;br&gt;- Golden Master Sword (Issuelink's OoT Master Sword, edited by Tach9, modified by Real Princess Zelda)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;Link's Awakening: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;- Mirror Shield (Asalazar Model)&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;Ocarina of Time:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;- Kokiri Sword (Smash Ultimate Model)&lt;br&gt;- Fairy Boomerang (Smash Ultimate model)&lt;br&gt;- Fairy Bow (Smash Ultimate model, rigging by Asalazar)&lt;br&gt;- Master Sword (Issuelink model, edited by Tach9)&lt;br&gt;- Deku Shield (Smash Ultimate model)&lt;br&gt;- Hylian Shield of Time (New model from MessyProduct and Asalazar)&lt;br&gt;- Megaton Hammer (Asalazar model)&lt;br&gt;- Gerudo Mirror Shield (&lt;a href="https://gamebanana.com/mods/167938"&gt;Issuelink model&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;br&gt;- Crescent Mirror Shield (&lt;a href="https://gamebanana.com/mods/167940"&gt;Issuelink model&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;br&gt;- Phantom Ganon's Spear (Asalazar model)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;Majora's Mask:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;- Kokiri Sword (MM) (Hyrule Warriors model)&lt;br&gt;- Ikana Mirror Shield (Issuelink model, modified by Tach9 and Asalazar)&lt;br&gt;- Razor Sword (&lt;a href="https://gamebanana.com/mods/443079"&gt;Asalazar model&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;br&gt;- Hero's Shield (&lt;a href="https://gamebanana.com/mods/443079"&gt;Asalazar model&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;br&gt;- Gilded Sword (Issuelink model)&lt;br&gt;- Hero's Bow (MM) (Asalazar model)&lt;br&gt;- Great Fairy Sword (Issuelink model)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;Minish Cap: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;- All four Elemental White Swords (&lt;a href="https://gamebanana.com/members/3273745"&gt;GenericVideoGameNPC model&lt;/a&gt;, modified by Real Princess Zelda, textures modified by TheRicoLicious and Real Princess Zelda)&lt;br&gt;- Four Sword (&lt;a href="https://gamebanana.com/members/3273745"&gt;GenericVideoGameNPC model&lt;/a&gt;, modified by Real Princess Zelda, textures modified by TheRicoLicious)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;Wind Waker:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;- Master Sword (Smash Ultimate model, modified by Tach9 and Asalazar)&lt;br&gt;- Mirror Shield (Hyrule Warriors model)&lt;br&gt;- Skull Hammer (WWHD model)&lt;br&gt;- Ganondorf's Swords (WWHD model)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;Phantom Hourglass:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;- Oshus's Sword (Modified Sword of the Hero model and textures from TotK, done by Real Princess Zelda)&lt;br&gt;- Phantom Sword (Hyrule Warriors model, modfied by Tach9 and Asalazar)&lt;br&gt;- Island Lobster Shield (Hyrule Warriors model)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;Spirit Tracks:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;- Lokomo Sword (Hyrule Warriors model, modified by Tach9 and Asalazar)&lt;br&gt;- Shield (Spirit Tracks model)&lt;br&gt;- Phantom Weapons (Smash Ultimate model)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;Twilight Princess:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;- Ordon Sword (TPHD model)&lt;br&gt;- Ordon Shield (TPHD model)&lt;br&gt;- Wooden Shield (TPHD model, modfied by Real Princess Zelda and Potatofried17)&lt;br&gt;- Hylian Shield of Twilight (TPHD model, modified by Asalazar)&lt;br&gt;- Master Sword of Twilight (Issuelink sword model, Asalazar sheath model)&lt;br&gt;- Hero's Bow (TPHD model)&lt;br&gt;- Gale Boomerang (TPHD model, textures redone by Liv.sterling)&lt;br&gt;- Darknut Sword/Shield (Hyrule Warriors model)&lt;br&gt;- Zant's Scimitars (Hyrule Warriors model)&lt;br&gt;- Scimitar of Twilight (TPHD model)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;Skyward Sword:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;- Sacred Bow (SSHD model)&lt;br&gt;- Goddess Shield (SSHD model)&lt;br&gt;- Demise's Sword (SSHD model)&lt;br&gt;- Ghirahim's Sword (SSHD model)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;Breath of the Wild:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;- Bow of Light&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;Echoes of Wisdom: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;- Sword of Might (&lt;a href="https://gamebanana.com/mods/590199"&gt;Chalmoro Azohen model&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://gamebanana.com/mods/596750"&gt;ported to TotK by charlie92155&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;br&gt;- Sword of Might Lvl 2 (&lt;a href="https://gamebanana.com/mods/590199"&gt;Chalmoro Azohen model&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://gamebanana.com/mods/596750"&gt;ported to TotK by charlie92155&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;br&gt;- Sword of Might Lvl 3 (&lt;a href="https://gamebanana.com/mods/590199"&gt;Chalmoro Azohen model&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://gamebanana.com/mods/596750"&gt;ported to TotK by charlie92155&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;Original Weapons: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;Lightning Cleaver (Based on a port of the Windcleaver from BotW, emissions done by Lye, recolored by Real princess Zelda)&lt;br&gt;Dark Bow (Modified Fairy Bow model)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;New enemies, mechanics, and more: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;Light Arrowheads:&lt;/span&gt; Since custom arrows are impossible, I made a workaround in the form of attachable Light Arrowheads that you attach to the end of your arrow. They work similarly to a Star Fragment, however, will do an additional 50 damage. They will only be added to your inventory when the Bow of Light or Dusk Bow are equipped.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;Mirror Essence:&lt;/span&gt; Instead of giving optional patches for mirror shield functionality, I decided to add a Mirror Essence item that you fuse to a mirror shield to give it the light reflecting functionality. The benefits to this is that your shield will not have a constant light beam in sunlight, even when not drawn. The items can only be added to your inventory when any mirror shield is equipped. While you can fuse them to arrows or weapons, if you try to fuse them to a non-mirror shield, all Mirror Essence fuses will be removed (even those fused to actual mirror shields).&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;New Enemies:&lt;/span&gt; Quite a few enemies and mini-bosses are added to this mod for collecting equipment. These enemies include the Darknut (Hyrule Warriors model, rigging by -Alpha-, textures of Liv.sterling), Phantom (Rigging by -Alpha-), Phantom Ganon ((OoT) Rigging by Potatofried17), Dark Link (Rigging by Potatofried17), and Illusion of Ganondorf.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;Sacred Weapon Spawning:&lt;/span&gt; The Master Swords and other sacred weapons (Four Sword, Phantom Sword, etc) will disappear when dropped, this is intended! These items will never show up in the shop and are designed to only allow for one of each weapon. However, if you somehow lose one of these weapons, simply press LR + A + D-pad Right and you can summon these weapons again!&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;Weapon Swapping:&lt;/span&gt; If you have one of the Magical Swords equipped, you can press R + A to swap between them at will! If you press A + B, you can swap the Four Sword ability!&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;Future Additions:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Link's Awakening:&lt;br&gt;- Koholint Sword&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Wind Waker:&lt;br&gt;- Hero's Sword&lt;br&gt;- Darknut Sword (WWHD Model)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Minish Cap:&lt;br&gt;- Broken Picori Sword&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Spirit Tracks:&lt;br&gt;- Bow of Light&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Skyward Sword:&lt;br&gt;- Master Sword (Unawakened)&lt;br&gt;- Goddess White Sword&lt;br&gt;- Goddess Longsword&lt;br&gt;- Wooden/Iron Shields&lt;br&gt;- Sacred and Divine Shields&lt;br&gt;- Bow&lt;br&gt;- Iron Bow&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Echoes of Wisdom: &lt;br&gt;- Bow of Might&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;Optional Patches:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;Unbreakable Patch:&lt;/span&gt; This patch will make all pieces of equipment unbreakable (even bows and shields) except for the Razor Sword, which has its durability increased to 100.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;Invisible Bows:&lt;/span&gt; This patch makes all of the bows invisible when not drawn, also makes quivers invisible. Has unbreakable and breakable options.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;Unbreakable Razor Sword:&lt;/span&gt; This patch makes the Razor Sword unbreakable.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;Compatiblity:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;This mod was made for versions 1.1.0, 1.1.1, 1.1.2, 1.2.0, and 1.2.1. THIS MOD HAS NOT BEEN TESTED ON ANY VERSIONS RELEASED AFTER 1.2.1, you can use TKMM for making it compatible with these versions, however.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;IMPORTANT!!! If you are using TKMM, then use the TKCL file instead!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;It is recommended this mod goes above any large mods such as Challenge Mode, Depths of the Kingdom, The Second Quest, and Dark Army Resurrection.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Places this mod over any mods that modify BGM_HyruleCastle_Ground.bwav and BGM_TempleOfTime_Sky.bwav if you want proper music in custom locations.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;When applying these patches manually, apply them in this order:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Weapons of Legend Redux&lt;br&gt;Unbreakable Patch&lt;br&gt;Invisible Bows Unbreakable&lt;br&gt;Razor Sword Unbreakable&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;Current known issues:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;- Custom locations have odd lighting&lt;br&gt;- Custom locations do not show up on map (Two are intentional, one I am looking into fixing)&lt;br&gt;- Mirror Shields show up dark in the inventory (Currently no known solution)&lt;br&gt;- Sometimes swapping your weapon does not equip it, just swap it again to fix this&lt;br&gt;- When pressing LR + A + D-pad Right during a parry, attack, or charge attack, Link will freeze in place. Usually you only have to wait about 10-20 seconds for the menu to appear. If not, either pause your game and swap a weapon or jump and you can move again.&lt;br&gt;- One of the chests in the Scorching Coliseum does not require you to defeat all enemies to open. Attempts have been made to fix this to no avail (just pretend it's a gift from the goddess)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b class="SelectedElement"&gt;IMPORTANT!!! If you experience any crashes, please, please, please test this mod again by itself with tkmm and without and go to the same area where you experienced the crash before reporting it! If you experience the crash again, please report it to me here or on Discord. When you report it, please provide this information:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;- Location where you experienced the crash&lt;br&gt;- What version of TotK you were running&lt;br&gt;- Whether it happened when using tkmm, on its own, or both.&lt;br&gt;- What emulator you are using (or Switch if you're using that)&lt;br&gt;- And if you are using an emulator, please provide what OS you are running.&lt;/b&gt;</description>
