    <item>
      <title>TotK 1.0.0 Speedrun Practice Mod</title>
      <author>Echocolat</author>
      <link>https://gamebanana.com/mods/594672</link>
      <comments>https://gamebanana.com/mods/594672#PostsListModule</comments>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">f098b5178f59078b13b088fc063f5af45e6cc2f6</guid>
      <pubDate>Tue, 28 Oct 2025 21:39:25 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6901348e188ae.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/68272b83ef616.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/68272ba4975ea.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/68272beaac06c.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/68272bffeeb67.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/68272c3fdb1ba.jpg"/&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Update:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;br&gt;&lt;em&gt;Addition&lt;/em&gt;: Added Fuse Entry, Fuse to Ultrahand and Ultrahand AS Fly "saves" in the mod menu&lt;br&gt;&lt;em&gt;Bugfix&lt;/em&gt;: Fixed Cog Skip Skip save not actually working&lt;br&gt;&lt;em&gt;Improvement&lt;/em&gt;: Made dzuggle x10 in saves post Ascend Overload Setup much more consistent (thanks dt)&lt;br&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;This mod is made for and works only on version 1.0.0&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Current version is 2.4. &lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;Make sure you're using english (either regions) or russian text or the mod menu will not work.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;h1&gt;Features&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Commands&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Y + X + A + B: Gives you a &lt;b&gt;fairy&lt;/b&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Y + A + Dpad Left: Stores your position and rotation into a &lt;b&gt;save state&lt;/b&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Y + A + Dpad Right: &lt;b&gt;Warps &lt;/b&gt;you at the saved position and rotation.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Y + A + Dpad Down: &lt;b&gt;Warps &lt;/b&gt;you at the correct location, in a free fall state, and gives you one fairy and two wings (execute on GSI for less lag), so that you can practice wing flip.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Y + A + Dpad Up: Triggers the end of the Demon King Ganondorf fight cutscene that leads to &lt;b&gt;Demon Dragon&lt;/b&gt;. Also gives Master Sword to speed up cutscenes, one Black Lizalfos Horn and two wings.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;X + A + Dpad Down: &lt;b&gt;Dzuggles &lt;/b&gt;your currently equipped weapon and reequips it. (made by the goat @dt13269)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;L3 + R3 + B: &lt;b&gt;Dzuggles &lt;/b&gt;100 times (well, zuggle drop it after 10 dzuggles) your currently equipped weapon. Not really useful for actual practice, but it's funny.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;ZL + ZR + R3: Triggers a BancChange in order to refresh the map actors as well as putting an AS bow on your back instead of at your feet.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;ZL + ZR + L3: Loads a "save" menu which allows you to load nine "saves" for now:&lt;ul dir="auto"&gt;&lt;li&gt;Prologue, which just boots Prologue with the correct loadout and no flag turned on.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Cog Skip Skip, which puts you just after Room of Awakening, in position to go in Cog Skip Skip, with the correct loadout and flags.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Wing Bridge to ToT, which puts you on a wing where the Golem use to stand, with the correct loadout and flags.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;FDC to Ascend, which puts you just after the void out after interacting with Temple of Time door for the first time, with the correct loadout and flags.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Ascend Overload Setup, which puts you inside the Ascend shrine, at the spot you do the dzuggles, with the correct loadout and flags.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Early Battery, which puts you in the cave below Ascend shrine, overloaded with 10 dzuggles, with the correct loadout and flags.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Fuse Entry, which puts you at the start of the Fuse shrine, overloaded with 10 dzuggles, with the correct loadout and flags.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Fuse to Ultrahand, which puts you at the end of the Fuse shrine, with Fuse shrine already completed, overloaded with 10 dzuggles, with the correct loadout and flags.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Ultrahand AS Fly, which puts you at the start of the Ultrahand shrine, overloaded with 10 dzuggles, with the correct loadout and flags.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Misc&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;100% topaz drop rate on Daruk amiibos.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Visuals on key trigger areas such as all relevant Prologue areas and the area triggering an autosave before Purah Pad.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Any triggered area other than the Ganondorf cutscene one in Prologue will reset Prologue.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;h1&gt;Notes&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Make sure to throw your weapon to remove any dzuggle past the "Ascend Overload Setup" save from the "save menu" before using it.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;Thanks to&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;:&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Real Princess Zelda and dt13269 for their help with setting up AINB&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Echecetdame for the original ideas of commands&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;MrMystery for Starlight&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;dt13269 for his AINB library&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;aquacluck for their lotuskit&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Arch Leaders for NX Editor&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;zeldamods/leoetlino for EventEditor&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li class="SelectedElement"&gt;Aergyl for the help on understanding glitches better&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;h1&gt;How to install&lt;/h1&gt;Make sure to delete any previous installation of the mod if you're updating. Note that this is not compatible with 99% of mods (but it is compatible with the Intro Skip mod).&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;h2&gt;If you're playing on emulator&lt;/h2&gt;Download the emulator version of the mod in the releases and extract the Practice Mod TotK 1.0.0 folder in your mod folder.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;h2&gt;If you're not using Simple Mod Manager&lt;/h2&gt;Download the normal version of the mod in the releases and extract the atmosphere folder from the archive in the root folder of your modded Switch's SD Card. Accept any file overwrite. To remove it, simply delete the exefs and &lt;code&gt;romfs&lt;/code&gt; folders in &lt;code&gt;atmosphere\contents\0100F2C0115B6000&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;h2&gt;If you're using Simple Mod Manager&lt;/h2&gt;Download the Simple Mod Manager version of the mod in the releases and extract the &lt;code&gt;mods&lt;/code&gt; folder from the archive in the root folder of your modded Switch's SD Card. Then you can enable the mod in Simple Mod Manager.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://files.gamebanana.com/mods/practicemodtotk100-v24.zip" type="application/zip"/>
      <media:content url="https://files.gamebanana.com/mods/practicemodtotk100-v24-smm.zip" type="application/zip"/>
      <media:content url="https://files.gamebanana.com/mods/practicemodtotk100-v24-emu.zip" type="application/zip"/>
      <category>Gameplay</category>
      <category>Gameplay</category>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Dark Army Resurrection</title>
      <author>miirkuz</author>
      <link>https://gamebanana.com/mods/453422</link>
      <comments>https://gamebanana.com/mods/453422#PostsListModule</comments>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">da704a78146b17c84b3511917218d18e6f30c08c</guid>
      <pubDate>Mon, 27 Oct 2025 21:20:37 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/649fe48b65e10.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/67fe4f03f1d4b.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/649fe45f8b37e.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/649fe45f52208.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/649fe46073fe8.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/649fe45f967c2.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/649fe459a9b16.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/649fe46050e68.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/649fe583f0fa5.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/649fe5847b52a.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/649fe5853ca46.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/649fe522db77e.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/64b5a9d2532b7.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/649fe45f42bad.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/649fe4593cf74.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/649fe4541d12e.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6548150b38343.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6548150c76bab.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6548150cb3708.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6548150d33933.jpg"/&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Update:&lt;/strong&gt; DAR 2.5&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;This version finally add compatibility for &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;Game Version 1.4.2&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; and Firmware &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;20.5.0&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; on both Switch and Emulators.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;This version require &lt;a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" href="https://tkmm.org/downloads/"&gt;TKMM 2.0 rc1&lt;/a&gt; to be installed.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Lots of new features have been added to make your journey more challenging, so be prepared!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;I highly recommend to start a new game using &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;DAR&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; paired with the brand new &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;DAR Overhaul&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;There is also a compatibility patch for &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;The Second Quest&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;, however at the moment &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;TSQ&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; is not 100% compatible with latest &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;TKMM&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; version so if you gonna play DAR + TSQ expect random chases.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;There are not any compatibility patches for &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;Challenge Mode&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;Depth of the Kingdom&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; since they are not updated to run with latest &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;TKMM&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;version.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;Changelog:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;- Added 'DAR Overhaul' module based on Kingdom Rebalanced&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;This overhaul is basically a lite version of &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;Kindom Rebalanced&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;mod made by &lt;a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" href="/members/1677174" data-id="1677174" data-label="Hollo" data-type="mention"&gt;@Hollo&lt;/a&gt;. His mod aims to fix TotK's fundamentally unbalanced elements – to 'tone down' its overly dependable mechanics and 'improve' alternatives – in an effort to expand the player's strategy.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;While I was testing DAR compatibilities, I've found out that Kindom Rebalanced is the perfect mod to match DAR mechanics, so I got the permission from &lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;Hollo (&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;Super Special Thanks to him&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; to make a Custom Overhaul based on his amazing mod.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Here a list of DAR Overhaul main features:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Rebalanced Damage Taken&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; – armours and enemies power work together to maintain a stable and flatter difficulty curve throughout the game. Upgrade requirements are listed in the armour description&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Rebalanced Loot and Bosses&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; – enemies health is proportional to the worth of their loot, and some bosses have adjusted health pools to provide a suitable challenge;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Rebalanced Weapons and Fusing&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; – fewer differences within weapon families, and fusing is less emphasized but remains a core mechanic&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Rebalanced Materials and Economy&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; – the rarer a material is, the better its properties. Potency is shown in the item description&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Upgradeable Armour&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; - enables armour upgrades for previously un-enhanceable armour pieces, except for the Well-Worn Hair Band&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Bows Changes&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; - Bows power now also reflect their range and rate-of-fire, and materials fused to them are stronger&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Shields Changes&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; - Shields no longer have Shield Guard, but several shields got new traits, from bashing to granting additional effects to fused weapons&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Enemies Changes&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; - Most enemies are less susceptible to staggering – Boss Bokoblin, Like Like, Gibdo, and Wizzrobe in particular have little to no stagger - Elemental enemies take significant damage from the opposite element, instead of suffering instant death&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Link's Attacks&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; - Some attacks deal increased damage (×1.5), such as charged attacks and chain attack finishers. Sneakstrikes deal less damage&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Food Changes&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; - Roasted materials can now grant brief special effects, and complex recipes grant significant healing and effect duration bonuses. Recipe bonuses are shown in the food description&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Mineru's Construct&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; has better mobility, power and defense&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Some Zonai Devices were improved&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;, such as the Wing and Light. The Fan was weakened to limit overreliance on simple hoverbikes&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Autobuild costs&lt;/em&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;were reduced for common building materials and increased for some Zonai devices&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Bugs are bigger&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;, to make them easier to spot&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Status Effects&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; are now simplified to two tiers and were rebalanced. Set bonuses no longer require upgrades&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Gloom Damage&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; is now almost instant on contact, and recovers slower&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Weapons no longer rank up&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; (Traveler -&amp;gt; Soldier, etc.) as you progress through the game.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;For detailed infos please refer to the official &lt;a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" href="https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/12eV97AZ33wgPFSNRZRd-nnXaCPi3481nb1nEOq4JJjU/edit?gid=552177921#gid=552177921"&gt;Detailed stat spreadsheet (weapons, armour, materials, recipes)&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;from Kingdom Rebalanced.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;DAR Overhaul&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; is highly recommended to be used with &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;DAR&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; alone or with &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;TSQ&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;- Added 'DAR Visual Enhancer' module&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;DAR Visual Enhancer will improve your visual experience with TOTK adding better Soulslike vibes&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span class="BlueColor"&gt;This module will be available only for Patreons.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://c10.patreonusercontent.com/4/patreon-media/p/post/142124586/67789832799e414bad9a94466c0737fc/eyJhIjoxLCJ3Ijo4MjB9/1.png?token-hash=Fz9JlCQOKzc4mYFDzq4glc6EiKc8GgcdgsqShgkp0a4%3D&amp;amp;token-time=1762819200"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;- Added 'DAR Compatibility Patch for Game Version 1.4.0+'&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;In order to play with Game Version 1.4.0+, you need to install this compatibility patch.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;- Added 'DAR Compatibility Patch for latest The Second Quest version'&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;- Added Easy Access to DAR Options&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Now you can open DAR Options menu anytime by pressing &lt;strong&gt;ZL + ZR + A&lt;/strong&gt;, this means that you can change setting everywhere without needing to find a Campfire anymore!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;This feature has been implemented by &lt;a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" href="/members/3228031" data-id="3228031" data-label="PrincessZelda" data-type="mention"&gt;@PrincessZelda&lt;/a&gt; so &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;Special Thanks&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; to her.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://c10.patreonusercontent.com/4/patreon-media/p/post/142124586/a2902d8fdab04c3985a485eaa77e6026/eyJhIjoxLCJ3Ijo4MjB9/1.png?token-hash=TfzlWQDoDFu_vx6JHqx_GNxgEYjannyagvK0xPi_efw%3D&amp;amp;token-time=1762819200"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;- Added Disable Enemies Spawning&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Added a new in game option where you can choose to Disable Spawning Enemies anytime you want. This will help you if you need no enemies spawning to complete quests. Note that Chuchus, Stone Pebblits, Keese, Aerocudas, and Stals will still Spawn.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://c10.patreonusercontent.com/4/patreon-media/p/post/142124586/b1d29bd0e83743f9a751a219414a20dd/eyJhIjoxLCJ3Ijo4MjB9/1.png?token-hash=KrmcpZaegWApNSAJjnAabHaFa5tcy7YN3Ve1Xj-jwUw%3D&amp;amp;token-time=1762819200"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;- DAR default options are highlighted in orange&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Now it is easier to check DAR default in game options.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;- Added more variety on Random Enemies equipment&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;This is a great add-on that will make fights more interesting since now Random Enemies can be equipped with Swords, Large Swords, Spears and Bows. Before this addidtion, for example Random Bokoblins would have always been equipped with Sword and Shield, from now they can also be equipped with Large Swords, Spears and Bows. This addition will affect all random spawned enemies!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://c10.patreonusercontent.com/4/patreon-media/p/post/142124586/2b8d35d797294a3cad7170caec388f75/eyJhIjoxLCJ3Ijo4MjB9/1.png?token-hash=kP_8LbnQ6RtzimSBRFWa8nF8ixcfgWyHixR8_S6NHEU%3D&amp;amp;token-time=1762819200"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;- Random Elemental Lizalfos will be equipped with elemental weapons&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Elemental Lizalfos have been added to the new spawing system and they gonna be equipped with elemental weapons.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;- Harder Sages Temples&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Added a new option where you can enable Random Elemental Lizalfos and Elemental Yigas Spawns inside Sages Temples, making Temples way more challenging. Here some details about which elemental enemies you'll find inside Temples:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Wind Temple&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; - Ice Lizalfos and Ice Yigas plus random regular enemies&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Fire Temple&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; - Fire Lizalfos and Fire Yigas plus random regular enemies&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Thunder Temple&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;em&gt; &lt;/em&gt;- Electric Lizalfos and Electric Yigas plus random enemies&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Water Temple&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; - All Elemental Lizalfos and all Elemental Yigas plus random enemies&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;You can choose the quantity of Elemental Lizalfos and Elemental Yigas in TKMM options.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span class="BlueColor"&gt;This option is customizable only for Patreons, while in free version is gonna be active with the 'Normal Quantity' value.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://c10.patreonusercontent.com/4/patreon-media/p/post/142124586/d63b426a9388405c8a642e8df1d6b665/eyJhIjoxLCJ3Ijo4MjB9/1.png?token-hash=SnB2U2X1nakdyXD2pzdNDu_UTymYaTkB5oaxofHRgTw%3D&amp;amp;token-time=1762819200"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;- Added New Elemental Yiga Archers&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;After you complete 1 temple or 20 Shrines, Elemental Yiga Archers have a probabilty to shoot arrows fused with Elemental Ores instead of Elemental Fruits. Now you need to pay extra attention to Elemental Yiga Archers.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;- Rebalanced Elemental Weapons&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Elemental Weapons Damage and Durability have been rebalanced to fit better the game experience with &lt;strong&gt;DAR Overhaul&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;- Changed 'Gloom Hands have 13 tentacles' to 'Gloom Hands have 7 tentacles' in 'Enemies Buffs'&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;This option has been changed since it wasn't balanced and it used to cause FPS drops. Now selecting this option Gloom Hands will have 7 tentacles instead of 5, making encounters with Gloom Hand more challenging.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span class="BlueColor"&gt;This option is customizable only for Patreons.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://c10.patreonusercontent.com/4/patreon-media/p/post/142124586/610e3b33d1df4598834c0f31e4e0fa42/eyJhIjoxLCJ3Ijo4MjB9/1.png?token-hash=pOv27p1ddUNf6iPb-odJxSHDCKKAEJIE9gQmy9_L4mo%3D&amp;amp;token-time=1762819200"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;- Added 'Koroks give more rewards' option in 'Miscellaneous'&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Selecting this option will give Koroks to have a chance to give more 1 to 3 Korok Seeds and 1 to 3 random items.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span class="BlueColor"&gt;This option is customizable only for Patreons, while in free version is gonna be active by default.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;- Added red sky when fighting Demon Lynels&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;This small addition will make Demon Lynels fights more scary.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://c10.patreonusercontent.com/4/patreon-media/p/post/142124586/34989555dee6402986a78dfd732c1bce/eyJhIjoxLCJ3Ijo4MjB9/1.png?token-hash=3IcRvW402651_dGKU3DcxZKBvBSt0aIeWp5UCEcOmZo%3D&amp;amp;token-time=1762819200"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;- Disable instant Break Life Heal&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Added an in game option under '&lt;strong&gt;Health Regeneration&lt;/strong&gt;' to disable instant Break Life Heal when activating Lightroots in the Dephts.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;- Improved 'Locked Chests' and 'Regular Chest'&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Added an option to choose the content of Regular Chests, if you play with 'Regular Chests' or 'Locked Chests', a dialog box will appear asking you if you wanna get Regualar or Randomized content, this will prevent you to get always Opals from random spawned chests.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Fixed first chest in Room of Awakening when using 'Locked Chests' or 'Regular Chests' option, now using this option you will get the Archaic Legwear.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Fixed first random chest after dying when using 'Locked Chests' or 'Regular Chests' option paired with 'Extreme Punitive Death' option, now after you died yo gonna get 3 random weapons and 2 random armor pieces from the first chest you open.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://c10.patreonusercontent.com/4/patreon-media/p/post/142124586/9c69df9b295e48488cd92984fc18905a/eyJhIjoxLCJ3Ijo4MjB9/1.png?token-hash=9qIqgUygnJNBJxch3Icf01ge-4qGE5m-LhMNzQMexeE%3D&amp;amp;token-time=1762819200"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;- Increased Random Spawing Chests&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;More Chests will randomly spaw around the map.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;- Rebalanced Random Spawing Enemies&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Random Enemies quantity have been rebalanced in order to get a better experience, expecially when using &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;DAR Overhaul&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;- Fixed 'Horn Drops Probability'&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Now the Horn drops Probablity will work as intended for all enemies.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span class="BlueColor"&gt;This option is customizable only for Patreons while in this FREE version is locked at 50%.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;How to Install&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;Inside the zip file you gonna find:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;DAR Compatibility Patch for Game Version 1.4.0+, DAR Compatibility Patch for TSQ 1.1, Dark Army Resurrection 2.5 - Free, DAR Overahul&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;You need &lt;a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" href="https://tkmm.org/downloads/"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;TKMM 2.0 rc1&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt; to install &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;DAR&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;When installing with &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;TKMM&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;make sure to follow this mod order:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;DAR Compatibility Patch for Game Version 1.4.0+ (only for game version 1.4.0 or higher)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;DAR Compatibility Patch for TSQ 1.1 (only if playing with TSQ)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;Dark Army Resurrection 2.5 - Deluxe (main module)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;DAR Overahul (optional)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;The Second Quest (optional)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;For more info check &lt;a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" href="https://dark-army-resurrection.fandom.com/wiki/DAR_for_Tears_of_the_Kingdom"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dark Army Resurrection TOTK Wiki&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;For support join &lt;a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" href="https://gamebanana.com/linkfilter?url=https%3A%2F%2Fdiscord.gg%2FXcrf7cSwP9&amp;amp;follow=true"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dark Army Discord Server&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;Thanks for all your support!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;ENJOY!!!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;What is Dark Army Resurrection?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;Dark Army Resurrection&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; is a mod that aims to create a brand new experience with &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;TOTK&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;, adding to the game some original and unique mechanics that will increase the difficulty, furthermore it will introduce a large number of customizable in-game options, simply by interacting with any campfire.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Here are some of the most popular&lt;strong class="SelectedElement"&gt; &lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;DAR&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;features:&#13;
&#13;
&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;Random Spawning Enemies System&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; - Enemies will randomly spawn all over the map, the more you progress in the game, the higher will be the enemies rank.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&#13;
&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;Gambling Chests&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; - All chests contain 1 to 3 items, some chests can be empty.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&#13;
&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;Locked Chests&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; - You need Chests Keys to open chests and Chests Keys are dropped by enemies.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&#13;
&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;Custom Moveset&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; - Use Double Jump and a brand new Combat System based on Random Combos, Limited Flurry Rush and Easy Perfect Parries.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&#13;
