    <item>
      <title>Playable Riju Mod</title>
      <author>#1RijuFan</author>
      <link>https://gamebanana.com/mods/627813</link>
      <comments>https://gamebanana.com/mods/627813#PostsListModule</comments>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">2a4d86859e6936249402309662c4e2f99b36ee24</guid>
      <pubDate>Sat, 18 Oct 2025 14:24:58 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/68f3a031dfbb9.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/68f3a00920cec.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/68f3a02f86ea5.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/68f3a02fb3730.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/68f3a009edddb.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/68f3a0098d1ba.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/68f3a0094c3b5.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/68f3a009b9ee2.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/68f3a02fd9fc4.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/68f3a02fe971d.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/68f3a02fb3020.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/68f3a02fde1ab.jpg"/&gt;&lt;br&gt;This mod makes Riju playable.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Some armor sets have been redesigned, but not all. A focus of the armor redesigns was the ability to mix and match them. Try mixing your favorite pieces and dyes (when applicable) to make unique combinations.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;If you would like to see all of the outfit changes, there is a document &#13;
linked below showcasing each one and which ones are dyeable.&lt;br&gt;https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1Daqs8OKPMXDIF4hdV29AkUXpHxBpYjXh6sKD3upEXnQ/edit?usp=sharing&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;== Features ==&lt;br&gt;Various aspects of Gerudo Town have been changed, such as:&lt;br&gt;* Visiting Underground Gerudo Town does not cause guards to start to escort the player out.&lt;br&gt;* The Voe and You class does not prevent Riju from visiting in the daytime.&lt;br&gt;* Riju can sleep in her bed.&lt;br&gt;And more!&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Talk to Cara (Isha's assistant in the jewlery store) in Gerudo Town after obtaining the Royal Gerudo Armor (replacement of the Knight’s armor) to change its style, or talk to her anytime to put on/take off the crown. Note that the crown may not appear depending on the head armor worn.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Complete the Pride of the Gerudo quest from Isha to obtain two Scimitars of the Seven. They do not break, but cannot be fused to.&lt;br&gt;Equipping the Scimitar for the shield slot enables different attack animations (even if a Scimitar is not equipped in the sword slot), where the last attack of a combo may be altered by holding the control stick forward (lunge attack) or back (combo attack).&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;img src="https://i.imgur.com/Sors2yW.gif"&gt;&lt;br&gt;Dash attack&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;img src="https://i.imgur.com/5Dim3Yo.gif"&gt;&lt;br&gt;Combo attack&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;img src="https://i.imgur.com/exripvV.gif"&gt;&lt;br&gt;Lunge attack&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Equipping both Scimitars causes lightning strikes when performing charged attacks.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Warning! This mod edits Player.asb, Player.pack, and various RSDB files. Use TKMM (https://tkmm.org/) to merge it with other mods. However, note that due to the mod editing various unmergable files such as Player.asb, it will not be compatible with mods that edit that file.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;== Known issues ==&lt;br&gt;Pre-rendered cutscenes and voice clips where Link’s name is said were not replaced due to the effort required to replace them faithfully. Therefore, the intro cutscene has been made skippable, and scripts for some of the pre-rendered scenes are left untouched.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;The script for TOTK is very large and testing in-game can require setting up various complicated save conditions. Therefore, there may be dialogue or text that doesn’t fit the situation or reads weird. If you find such text please let us know!&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;The all versions variant may not work via TKMM due to the 1.4.0 GameData.&#13;
 If you are having issues try to delete the &#13;
GameData/GameDataList.Product.140.byml.zs file and install via the &#13;
folder instead. (Thanks to mr.the for finding this out!)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;This mod is not compatible with 1.0.0 or 1.3.0.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;This mod was primarily tested on Switch 1.1.2 / Yuzu 1.2.1. There may be issues with other configurations.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
